-- Canada Stocks Snap Two-Day Drop as Oil Rallies on Cyprus Options
-- B y   E r i c   L a m
-- 2013-03-20T14:19:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-20/canada-stocks-snap-two-day-drop-as-oil-rallies-on-cyprus-options.html
Canadian  stocks  rose for the first
time in three days as oil rallied from its biggest plunge in a
month while European policy makers weighed bailout options for
Cyprus.  Canadian Natural Resources Ltd. and  Suncor Energy Inc. (SU) ,
Canada’s largest oil producer, gained at least 0.4 percent.
BlackBerry climbed 5.7 percent as an analyst at Morgan Stanley
raised his rating on the smartphone maker’s stock. Valeant
Pharmaceuticals International Inc. added 3.5 percent after
agreeing to buy Obagi Medical Products Inc.  The  Standard & Poor’s/TSX Composite Index (SPTSX)  rose 35.90
points, or 0.3 percent, to 12,809.77 at 10:14 a.m. in Toronto.
The S&P/TSX has risen 3 percent this year.  Oil climbed as much as 1.1 percent after Luxembourg’s Luc
Frieden called for fellow euro-area finance ministers to
assemble a new rescue package for Cyprus. The island nation
rejected a levy on bank deposits yesterday, causing crude
futures to tumble.  Investors also await the U.S. Federal Reserve’s latest
monetary policy decision, due at 2 p.m. in  New York .  To contact the reporter on this story:
